	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 23rd 12:56 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>my main is a warrior, i have several alts, but i keep coming back to my warrior i love him so much. just so u know now, i am level 17, highest iv ever been, so all of you who think newbies are stupid can just skip this post now. anyways, i am a barbarian warrior. i dont know why i chose this i just did, certainly not for stats, or the fact that i cant see in the dark...but that doesnt matter. imo starting atributes only affect so much. items can enhance your stats very easily, so dont stress out on what to put your stats into as a warrior, you should be more concerned with what your character looks like, youll be seeing through his eyes all your life and its nice to pick one you think you could role play well, if thats your thing. creating out of the way, i dlike to give a brief summary of where i fought to gain my levels. of course, as a barbarian, i started in halas, and stayed there for my first few levels, and eventually left at level 5. i first killed gnoll pups, then polar bear cubs, then more polar bear cubs...and yet more polar bear cubs. even though the cubs will be blue at level 4, it is a decent way to get your weapon skills up and sometimes you wolll come accross a HQ bear pelt and make 25 platinum off of it. after level 5, i made my way to east commons. mind you level 5 in EC is not great, there are very few even con monsters to fight, but a small group of maybe 2 or 3 people around level 5 works great not only to gain experience (killing pumas mainly), but also to make friends. its important to make good trust worthy friends early in life, easpecially as a class that later on will not be able to solo efficantly. make sure to put people on your friends list so that if you see someone and they say hi, u remember me? and you dont, well, its gonna be kinda embarasing. also u can check friend list for people to level with if you have no group. joining a guild is also a great way to make friends, although at low levels few people in your guild wil be able to group with you. anyway, once achieving level 6 in EC i grouped on and off, ocasionally soloing pumas for good experience if i could find even cons. then at 7 i soloed up to 8 easily with pumas and rattle snakes, until i was level 8, the average acceptanced level for orc camps, which brought me up to level 11 in little time. at level 11 orcs will give little experience, yet derv groups in nro or wc dont always accept level 11 people. i chose to go to wc and kill young kodiaks alone for my 11th level, as it gave me good experience and ocasionally a hq bear skin. the only downside to this is young kodiaks are ofton quite nasty and even cons may sometimes kill you. luckyfully, guards will help you if ever you need. willowhisps are also i good choice for level 11s to hunt, but for my 11th level unfortunately there were none to be found, a guild had probably 20 level 12 people killing whips just for gls which sell for 6-7pp to players (also part of a quest), so i was unable to find any wisps to kill. come level 12, most derve groups will welcome you and can take you from level 12 up to about 15 fairly easily. once you reach 15, going to oasis is a good choice, crocs and camiens at the waters edge give good experience, but crap for loot. at level 16 you could go to lake of ill omen, lots of even cons and some blues (however, be careful, more are red, very red). i fought at the windmill, pulling to the back until i got to level 17. good fast experience, however long downtimes because warriors cant heal themselves passed 50 % health with bind woulnd. if you want grouping is possible at the mill, but in my experience you gain levels faster soloing than in a group most of the time, despite warrior dowtime. just make sure ot have bind wound maxed out. another place i went to a lot is befallen, now that it is changed, there is great loot (grey sr aprentice robes are lore so ppl dont loot more than one and they sell for 2 plat to vendors), but very dangerous. thats why i chose to go ther eonly for money not experience. people there have no problem with you looting the aprentice robes, they just keep the anoying corpses there longer. this is where i am now, level 17, still in LOIO, having a great time.i hope my experiences can benefit someone in some way...well, iv spent too much time here, u all probably are bored to death. safe travels to you all, and have fun always. =)&nbsp;&nbsp;  Brexin, 17th warrior of Halas<br>&nbsp;<br>penguin</td></tr>
