	   <tr><td colspan=2>responding to the question of the hybrid, warriors have higher STA, so they have higher base HP, and-the biggie- they can dual wield, the only other tank classes that can DW are ranger, monk and rouge, and none can hope to match a high str warrior on dmg, also those classes don't have the hp or the AC to square off with higher lvl mobs, when u get to your grouping days 30 or so +, on the other hand. Also, not only can a warrior DW but he also double hits and crits, but a ranger can do that as well, but remember rangers have the least hp/ac of any tank with thier base stats and without items.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, warriors r not the best tank class in all situations, if u r in close quarters u will need a SK to keep the creature from bouncing from cleric to caster to warrior, SK's have the best hatelist building spells, making them the most effective taunters when used in conjunction with the actual taunt skill, all the other classes have little things like this they r better at than warriors, n e way back to the original subject, hybrid spells r very useful, but by no means wonderful.. wait till u a lvl 30 ranger trying to heal yourself and u will know what i mean, or a lvl 30 SK praying your pet will make a difference ), after 30 tho the hybrid classes start looking up, but pre 30 they r a rather tuff number to play.<br><br>Best warrior classes.. that depends on how u wanna play it, if u r going to go for the effective damager Troll, Ogre, or barbarian, IMO troll is the most effective since they have twice the regen of other classes, as well as nearly the STA and STR of an ogre, i just threw the barbie in in case u wanted to be a good guy ), bear in mind, as a troll or ogre, u will do more dmg per hit, making u ideal for a 2hander weapon, but until u get your dexterity up with items u will not crit or cripple hit often, learn your combat skills very quickly or double or dual wield hit as often.<br><br>However, if u go with another race such as a woodelf, dark elf, or human, etc, u will not hit for as much maximum per hit (due to low str) but your dexterity will cause u to double hit, DW, crit and cripple more, making u (depending on weapons) a superior dmgr with DW, but, u will not be able to stand toe to toe and take the hits a troll or ogre can.<br><br>So basically, high DEX race if u wanna play the part of the warrior who doesn't taunt, High STR/STA race if u wanna be the clumsy oaf who can take a lotta dmg.<br><br>Personally, i think that the Troll or iksar is the best choice for a warrior, higher regen rates on them, and decent STR/DEX/STA on all of them, just make sure u get your troll's dex up as quickly as possible if u choose that class (bear in mind, Ogres have the highest STR/STA combo in the game, so others may say they are the best, but the regen helps u to lvl faster thru the lower lvls, and the STR/STA diff can be quickly taken care of with jewelry and items<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
